<div data-type="problem" id="fs-id1170572106890"><div data-type="title">Evaluating a Limit Using a Table of Functional Values 1</div>
<p id="fs-id1170571596728">Evaluate <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><semantics><mrow><mrow><munder><mrow><mtext>lim</mtext></mrow><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo stretchy="false">&#8594;</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></munder><mfrac><mrow><mtext>sin</mtext><mspace width="0.1em"/><mi>x</mi></mrow><mi>x</mi></mfrac></mrow></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content"><mrow><munder><mrow><mtext>lim</mtext></mrow><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo stretchy="false">&#8594;</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></munder><mfrac><mrow><mtext>sin</mtext><mspace width="0.1em"/><mi>x</mi></mrow><mi>x</mi></mfrac></mrow></annotation-xml></semantics></math> using a table of functional values.</p>
</div>
<div data-type="solution" id="fs-id1170572552454">
<p id="fs-id1170572169167">We have calculated the values of <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><semantics><mrow><mrow><mi>f</mi><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow><mo>=</mo><mrow><mrow><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mtext>sin</mtext><mspace width="0.1em"/><mi>x</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow><mtext>/</mtext><mi>x</mi></mrow></mrow></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content"><mrow><mi>f</mi><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow><mo>=</mo><mrow><mrow><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mtext>sin</mtext><mspace width="0.1em"/><mi>x</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow><mtext>/</mtext><mi>x</mi></mrow></mrow></annotation-xml></semantics></math> for the values of <em data-effect="italics">x</em> listed in <a href="#fs-id1170572208852" class="autogenerated-content">[link]</a>.</p>
