<p id="fs-id1170571652076">The function <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><semantics><mrow><mrow><mi>f</mi><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow><mo>=</mo><mrow><mn>1</mn><mtext>/</mtext><mrow><msup><mrow><mrow><mo>(</mo><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow><mo>)</mo></mrow></mrow><mn>4</mn></msup></mrow></mrow></mrow></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content"><mrow><mi>f</mi><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow><mo>=</mo><mrow><mn>1</mn><mtext>/</mtext><mrow><msup><mrow><mrow><mo>(</mo><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow><mo>)</mo></mrow></mrow><mn>4</mn></msup></mrow></mrow></mrow></annotation-xml></semantics></math> has a vertical asymptote of <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><semantics><mrow><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>&#8722;3</mn><mo>.</mo></mrow></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content"><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>&#8722;3</mn><mo>.</mo></mrow></annotation-xml></semantics></math></p>
