<div data-type="problem" id="fs-id1170572499829">
<p id="fs-id1170572499831">Use the preceding two exercises to conjecture (guess) the value of the following limit: <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><semantics><mrow><mrow><munder><mrow><mtext>lim</mtext></mrow><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo stretchy="false">&#8594;</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></munder><mfrac><mrow><mtext>sin</mtext><mspace width="0.1em"/><mi>a</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow><mi>x</mi></mfrac></mrow></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content"><mrow><munder><mrow><mtext>lim</mtext></mrow><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo stretchy="false">&#8594;</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></munder><mfrac><mrow><mtext>sin</mtext><mspace width="0.1em"/><mi>a</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow><mi>x</mi></mfrac></mrow></annotation-xml></semantics></math> for <em data-effect="italics">a</em>, a positive real value.</p>
</div>
<div data-type="solution" id="fs-id1170572499869">
<p id="fs-id1170572499871"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><semantics><mrow><mrow><munder><mrow><mtext>lim</mtext></mrow><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo stretchy="false">&#8594;</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></munder><mfrac><mrow><mtext>sin</mtext><mspace width="0.1em"/><mi>a</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow><mi>x</mi></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mi>a</mi></mrow></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content"><mrow><munder><mrow><mtext>lim</mtext></mrow><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo stretchy="false">&#8594;</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></munder><mfrac><mrow><mtext>sin</mtext><mspace width="0.1em"/><mi>a</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow><mi>x</mi></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mi>a</mi></mrow></annotation-xml></semantics></math></p>
</div>
</div>
