</section>
<div data-type="glossary"><h3 data-type="glossary-title">Glossary</h3>
<dl id="fs-id1170572541944">
<dt>infinite limit</dt>
<dd id="fs-id1170572541950">A function has an infinite limit at a point <em data-effect="italics">a</em> if it either increases or decreases without bound as it approaches <em data-effect="italics">a</em></dd>
</dl>
<dl id="fs-id1170572467930">
<dt>intuitive definition of the limit</dt>
<dd id="fs-id1170572467935">If all values of the function <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><semantics><mrow><mrow><mi>f</mi><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow></mrow></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content"><mrow><mi>f</mi><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow></mrow></annotation-xml></semantics></math> approach the real number <em data-effect="italics">L</em> as the values of <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><semantics><mrow><mrow><mi>x</mi><mrow><mo>(</mo><mrow><mo>&#8800;</mo><mi>a</mi></mrow><mo>)</mo></mrow></mrow></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content"><mrow><mi>x</mi><mrow><mo>(</mo><mrow><mo>&#8800;</mo><mi>a</mi></mrow><mo>)</mo></mrow></mrow></annotation-xml></semantics></math> approach <em data-effect="italics">a</em>, <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><semantics><mrow><mrow><mi>f</mi><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow></mrow></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content"><mrow><mi>f</mi><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow></mrow></annotation-xml></semantics></math> approaches <em data-effect="italics">L</em></dd>
</dl>
<dl id="fs-id1170572467997">
<dt>one-sided limit</dt>
<dd id="fs-id1170572468002">A one-sided limit of a function is a limit taken from either the left or the right</dd>
</dl>
<dl id="fs-id1170572468006">
<dt>vertical asymptote</dt>
<dd id="fs-id1170572468012">A function has a vertical asymptote at <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><semantics><mrow><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>a</mi></mrow></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content"><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>a</mi></mrow></annotation-xml></semantics></math> if the limit as <em data-effect="italics">x</em> approaches <em data-effect="italics">a</em> from the right or left is infinite</dd>
</dl>
</div></body>

</html>